Voice Set Registration
  
  
  
In v1.16 voice sets can now be registered to what I call the registry (creative, yes).
  
  
The registry system offers a way to add voice sets from different mods to OSSO's editing features.
  
  
You simply drop the files in the OStim voice set folder, open the MCM Voice Sets page, select the voice set from the right drop-down and then select the sex and then whether or not you want to add it to auto assign. Wait... Auto Assign?
  
  
  
Auto Assign Feature
  
  
In v1.16 voice sets can now be auto assigned on scene start.
  
  
There are three options (selectable in the MCM, you can also disable it entirely):Â 
  
You can Auto assign the OSSO default (once), you can Randomly auto assign a voice set (once), or you can Always Assign a random voice set.
  
  
If you are using a single time auto assign, the voice set will be applied to the person at the start of the scene if they have the OStim default voice set, if you are using always auto assign then it will always assign a random voice set.
  
  
\* Auto assign features are sex specific
  
  
\* If you add more than one person to the start of the scene then it will only apply to the person you were looking at
  
  
\* The player has a default OSSO voice assigned when you first install the mod.

Load order
  
  
  
Install via mod manager. Overwrite both OStim SA and OStim Community Resources. Keep OStim and OSSO as high as you can in your load order to prevent issues.
  
  
  
Updating
  
  
  
Updating from v1.15 to v1.16 does not require a new game. But, there are massive changes and many removed forms and renamed scripts. From my testing it is safe and works perfectly fine, but if you have issues it may require a fresh start.
  
  
If updating from a version prior to v1.14, you will have a missing file error when loading the game. The esp was renamed in this update.
  
  
  
Uninstalling
  
  
  
As for any mod with scripts, it's not advised to uninstall it mid play-through. But, if you do, useÂ [ReSaver](https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/5031/). It is a great tool for cleaning up loose ends.
